theorem closure_eq_closure_interior_closure_of_P1
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (h : Topology.P1 A) :
    closure A = closure (interior (closure A)) := by
  apply subset_antisymm
  ·
    -- First, upgrade the `P1` inclusion to the desired target.
    have hA : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := by
      -- `h` gives `A ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
      have h₁ : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A) := h
      -- `interior A ⊆ interior (closure A)` by monotonicity,
      -- hence their closures satisfy the same inclusion.
      have h₂ : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := by
        apply closure_mono
        exact interior_mono (subset_closure : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure A)
      exact h₁.trans h₂
    -- Taking closures yields the required inclusion.
    have : closure A ⊆ closure (closure (interior (closure A))) :=
      closure_mono hA
    simpa [closure_closure] using this
  ·
    -- The reverse inclusion is immediate from `interior_subset`.
    exact closure_mono
      (interior_subset : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A)

theorem P1_iff_P3_of_open_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hOpenCl : IsOpen (closure (A : Set X))) :
    Topology.P1 A ↔ Topology.P3 A := by
  exact
    ⟨fun hP1 => Topology.P3_of_P1_and_open_closure (A := A) hP1 hOpenCl,
      fun hP3 => Topology.P1_of_P3_and_open_closure (A := A) hP3 hOpenCl⟩

theorem interior_closure_eq_closure_of_open_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hOpen : IsOpen (closure (A : Set X))) :
    interior (closure A) = closure A := by
  simpa using hOpen.interior_eq
